      h2.text-center 2002

      p I'm 17 and together with another colleague, we are skipping classes. After getting the traditional Giant Shaorma from the Tomis Port, we are heading towards the Casino. The building doesn't look too good, but we don't care. We are young the only thing that matters for us is that the Casino has a pool table. We are making the effort to walk such a huge distance onlyh because this the cheapest place in town where we can play pool. We are getting inside in the left wing of the Casino and the first thing I notice is the smoke smell impregnated in the walls. We are the only clients there. There is a bar and lots of alchohol bottles on the walls of the bar but we don't drink. The pool table is really old, the cues are old as well, we are barely able to play. After half an hour we get pissed and leave.

