      h2.text-center 2015

      p I'm back in my old hometown for a few days and now I'm heading towards the Casino to take some pictures of it. I already know that it's a ruin now and I want to take some pictures of it before they renovate it. This is of course, a joke, as nobody has any plan to do it. They promised many years in a row to renovate it, but until now they didn't do anything.

      p Getting closer and closer to the seafront, I'm starting to notice the smell. Strong and salty like always! I finally feel like home! The Casino is indeed a ruin, lots of people are walking around it, many taking pictures and selfies. There is no orchestra, like in the glorious days, 100 years ago. Instead an accordionist together with his cat is entertaining everybody who passes by and everybody seems to be happy. I'm happy too!

